## Page 2 — Status Tracker

### Page Purpose
The operational heartbeat of the sprint. Designed for speed — open it, see the current state, make updates, close it. Used in weekly standups, individual check-ins, and quick founder reviews. Every update made here feeds all downstream synthesis.

### Page Layout

**Top Section — Sprint Header**
Persistent across all views on this page:
- Sprint goal statement — always visible, styled as a banner (not collapsible)
- Quarter label and days remaining
- Summary bar — four metrics displayed horizontally:
  - Overall completion: percentage of milestones marked Complete
  - Initiatives: X Active / Y Complete / Z Blocked
  - Pace: On Track / At Risk / Off Track — a label only, not a calculated velocity. This is a founder-set field — they manually update it based on their read of the quarter. Rationale: calculated pace from milestone completion rates creates false precision given the intentional back-loading or front-loading of some initiatives. The founder's judgment is more accurate here.
  - Days remaining: countdown

**Filter Bar**
Below the header, above the milestone table:
- Filter by: 3P Column / Initiative / Owner / Status / Timeframe (month)
- All filters are multi-select
- "Clear All Filters" link appears when any filter is active
- Active filter state is remembered within the session but resets on page reload — no persistent filter state

**Main Content — Milestone Table**
The primary view. Each row is one milestone.

Columns:
| Column | Content | Editable |
|---|---|---|
| Select | Checkbox — for bulk status updates | Yes |
| Milestone | Parent initiative (muted, small) above milestone name (bold) | No — click opens milestone card modal |
| Status | Dropdown: Not Started / In Progress / Complete / Blocked | Yes — inline |
| Owner | Avatar + name | No — edit in milestone card modal |
| Timeframe | Month target | No — edit in milestone card modal |
| Notes | Free text, single line. Expandable on click. | Yes — inline |

**Row interactions:**
- Clicking the milestone name opens the full milestone card modal for editing
- Status column is directly editable inline — clicking the status cell opens a dropdown
- Notes field is directly editable inline — clicking activates the field
- Blocked status adds a subtle amber left border to the entire row
- Complete status adds a muted strikethrough to the milestone name and a green check to the status cell
- Rows can be selected via checkbox for bulk status update (e.g., select 3 milestones → mark all Complete)

**Grouped View Toggle**
Above the filter bar, a toggle between:
- **Flat view** (default): all milestones in a single table, sorted by timeframe then status
- **Grouped by Initiative view**: milestones nested under their parent initiative, collapsible by initiative. Initiative row shows initiative name, owner, completion percentage, and status badge.

**Add Notes / Standup Mode**
A "Standup Mode" toggle in the top right of the table area. When active:
- Columns simplify to: Milestone, Owner, Status, Notes
- Table rows expand slightly for easier reading on a projected screen
- A "This Month's Focus" banner appears at the top of the table, automatically filtering to show only milestones targeted for the current month — this is the standup's starting point
- Toggling off returns to the standard table view

### Data Sources
| Element | Source |
|---|---|
| Milestone list | milestones table joined to initiatives and capability_selections |
| Status updates | milestones table — status field, updated on change |
| Notes | milestones table — notes field |
| Pace label | sprints table — pace field, founder-set |
| Completion percentage | Calculated: count(status=Complete) / count(*) per sprint |

### No AI on This Page
Deliberate. The status tracker is a human-maintained ground truth surface. AI synthesis happens on the Momentum Synthesis page, drawing from data updated here.

### Empty & Edge States
- No milestones yet: prompt to complete sprint planning and add milestones before launching
- All milestones complete: celebratory state — "All milestones marked complete. Your sprint is ready for retrospective." with CTA to begin retrospective
- Sprint locked with no updates in 14+ days: a gentle banner — "No updates logged in 14 days. Consider reviewing progress before your next team check-in." — dismissible

