## Page 3 — Momentum Synthesis

### Page Purpose
The founder's periodic strategic read on the quarter. Not a dashboard of metrics — a synthesized, narrative account of where the sprint stands and what it means. Always founder-initiated. Generated fresh from current sprint data on demand.

### Page Layout

**Top Section — Sprint Context**
- Sprint goal statement — persistent banner
- Quarter label, days elapsed, days remaining
- Last synthesis date: "Last generated: [date and time]"
- "Generate New Synthesis" button — primary CTA, always visible

**Primary Content — Synthesis Display**

When no synthesis has been generated yet:
- Empty state: "When you're ready for a strategic read on your quarter, generate your first momentum synthesis below."
- A brief description of what the synthesis covers
- "Generate Synthesis" button

When a synthesis exists:
Three sections displayed in sequence, each visually distinct:

**Section 1 — Progress Narrative**
Two to three paragraphs. Written in second person, addressed to the founder. Covers:
- What has been completed so far and what that represents
- What is currently in motion
- An honest account of what has not yet been started and what that implies (without projecting failure)

**Section 2 — Attention Signal**
One to two specific observations surfaced from the data. Formatted as a distinct callout block, separate from the narrative. Examples:
- "Your Prioritize area 'Cash Flow Forecasting' has no milestone activity logged this month."
- "Two of your three Plant initiatives have been seeded — you're ahead of pace in this bucket."
- "Three milestones are currently flagged as Blocked. Two share the same owner — it may be worth a direct conversation."

These are observations, not alerts. The language is neutral and coaching-oriented. The platform is not judging — it is noticing.

**Section 3 — Encouragement Layer**
One paragraph. Specific to what this founder has accomplished, at their stage, given what it takes to do strategic development work while running an agency. Not generic. Not formulaic. The GPT prompt specifically instructs against generic praise — the encouragement must be grounded in the actual work done.

**Bottom of Page — Generation History**
A collapsed list of previous synthesis generations, each showing the date generated and the first line of the Progress Narrative. Expanding a historical entry shows the full synthesis from that date — so the founder can track how the narrative has evolved across the quarter.

### AI Behavior on This Page

**Input context provided to GPT:**
- Full sprint record (goal, initiatives, milestones, classifications, owners)
- Current status of every milestone
- Notes logged in the status tracker
- Days elapsed and remaining
- Founder's AE Ladder stage
- Maturity scores for selected capability areas
- Blockers flagged (status = Blocked)
- Capability areas with zero milestone activity since sprint lock
- Date of last synthesis (so GPT knows how much time has passed and can calibrate appropriately)

**System prompt guidance for GPT:**
- Write in second person, addressed directly to the founder
- Do not project or predict — describe what has happened and what is currently true
- Attention signals must be grounded in specific data points — no generic observations
- Encouragement must reference specific completions or efforts — not generic motivational language
- Maintain the platform's tone: sophisticated, observational, peer-level — not corporate, not cheerleading

**Regeneration:**
Each generation is timestamped and stored. The founder can generate as many times as they want. The display always shows the most recent generation. Historical generations are accessible below.

### Data Sources
| Element | Source |
|---|---|
| Sprint and milestone data | sprints, initiatives, milestones tables |
| Milestone activity | milestones table — status change timestamps |
| Blockers | milestones where status = Blocked |
| Generation history | momentum_syntheses table |
| AI output | GPT synthesis — stored on generation |

### Edge States
- Sprint just launched (< 7 days): synthesis available but a note acknowledges limited data — "Your sprint is just getting started. Generate a synthesis any time, though the picture will grow clearer as the quarter progresses."
- Sprint complete (retrospective pending): synthesis available but a banner prompts: "Your sprint is complete. Consider beginning your retrospective for a full-quarter synthesis."

