## Page 4 — Sprint Wind-Down

### Page Purpose
A structured closing process for the final weeks of the sprint. Helps the founder make deliberate decisions about what to close, what to carry forward, and what to release — and begins seeding context for the next quarter's planning cycle.

### Trigger & Availability
- Not accessible until the final 21 days of the sprint (3 weeks out)
- A contextual prompt appears on the Execution Overview and in the sidebar navigation when this threshold is reached: "Q1 ends in 21 days. Begin your wind-down review."
- Once triggered, it remains accessible through the end of the sprint
- After the sprint closes, this page becomes read-only — its decisions are locked into the retrospective and next sprint's context

### Page Layout

**Top Section**
- Sprint goal statement — persistent banner
- Days remaining — shown prominently with a sense of intentionality, not alarm
- Wind-down progress: a simple checklist showing which of the three wind-down steps have been completed:
  - [ ] Completion decisions made
  - [ ] Rollover items reflected on
  - [ ] Forward-seeding questions answered

**Step 1 — Completion Decisions**
A list of every incomplete initiative and milestone, grouped by 3P bucket. For each item, the founder makes a decision:

Initiative level:
- Each incomplete initiative shows: name, capability area, success definition, current milestone completion (e.g., "3 of 5 milestones complete"), owner
- Three decision options per initiative:
  - **Complete by end of sprint** — founder commits to finishing in remaining time. Milestone view expands to show which milestones are still open.
  - **Roll Over** — carry into next sprint. Triggers Step 2 reflection prompt for this initiative.
  - **Release** — no longer relevant or deprioritized. A brief confirmation: "Are you sure? This initiative will be archived and won't appear in next quarter's planning."

Milestone level (shown within each initiative):
- Individual milestones can be marked complete, rolled over, or released independently of the parent initiative's decision
- A milestone marked Complete here updates its status in the Status Tracker in real time

**Step 2 — Rollover Reflection**
Shown only for items marked "Roll Over" in Step 1. For each rolled-over initiative:
- Initiative name and original success definition shown as context
- Two prompted fields:
  - "What got in the way of completing this?" (free text, optional)
  - "Does this still belong in Prioritize next quarter, or has it shifted?" (dropdown: Still Prioritize / Move to Plant / Reassess during planning)
- These answers are stored and passed as context to the Quarter Map in the next sprint cycle

**Step 3 — Forward-Seeding Questions**
Three prompted reflection questions. Free text. Optional but encouraged. Shown after Steps 1 and 2 are complete.

1. "What surprised you most about this quarter — what went better or harder than expected?"
2. "Which capability area ended up needing more attention than you gave it?"
3. "If you were starting the quarter over, what would you classify differently?"

These answers feed the Retrospective synthesis and pre-populate context for next quarter's planning session.

**Wind-Down Summary**
After all three steps are addressed, the page shows a summary block:
- Initiatives completing by end of sprint: [N]
- Initiatives rolling over: [N]
- Initiatives released: [N]
- Milestones completing: [N]
- Milestones rolling over: [N]

A "Finalize Wind-Down" CTA appears when all items have a decision. Finalizing does not close the sprint — it simply locks the wind-down decisions and marks Step 4 of the wind-down checklist complete. The retrospective is a separate action.

### AI Behavior on This Page
Light. GPT is used for one output only:

**Wind-Down Summary Narrative:**
After the founder finalizes wind-down, GPT generates a single paragraph summarizing the decisions made — what is being completed, what is being carried forward, and what is being released. This paragraph is used as the opening context in the Retrospective synthesis. It is shown at the bottom of the wind-down page for founder review.

### Data Sources
| Element | Source |
|---|---|
| Incomplete initiatives | initiatives table — completion status |
| Incomplete milestones | milestones table — status != Complete |
| Completion decisions | wind_down_decisions table (new) |
| Rollover reflections | wind_down_reflections table (new) |
| Forward-seeding answers | sprint_reflections table (new) |
| Wind-down summary | GPT synthesis — stored in sprint_reflections |

