## Cross-Page Elements

### Execution Overview Page
The landing page for the Execution section (currently shown in Image 1 of the screenshots). Needs to serve as the navigation hub and status summary for the active sprint.

Should display:
- Sprint goal statement — prominent
- Sprint status: ACTIVE / WIND-DOWN / CLOSED
- Quick stats: overall milestone completion %, days remaining
- Four navigation cards (replacing or expanding the current two-card layout):
  - Sprint Launch — "View your sprint summary and share with your team"
  - Status Tracker — "Update milestone progress and run your weekly standup"
  - Momentum Synthesis — "Get a strategic read on your quarter" + last generated date
  - Sprint Wind-Down — appears only when within 21 days of sprint end
  - Retrospective — appears only when sprint is closed and wind-down is finalized
- No AI on this page — purely navigational and status-oriented

### Sprint Goal Persistence
The sprint goal statement appears as a persistent banner on every page in the execution section. It is never collapsible. It is always the first piece of content below the page header. This is a platform-wide design rule for the execution layer — the goal is always in view.

### Sprint History
Once a sprint is closed, all five pages become read-only historical records. A sprint history view (accessible from the execution overview) shows all past sprints with their retrospective summaries, capability score movements, and completion rates. This is the longitudinal record that compounds in value over multiple quarters.

